   },
   "source": [
    "In Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA), \n",
    "a negative Enrichment Score (ES) paired with a significant GSEA p-value ($p < 0.05$) does not indicate a weak or invalid result. \n",
    "\n",
    "Instead, the sign of the ES merely represents the direction of the biological alteration. \n",
    "A negative ES signifies that the genes within the specified pathway are predominantly down-regulated in the primary phenotype \n",
    "(e.g., the Relapse group) and localized at the bottom of the ranked list. \n",
    "\n",
    "Multiple immune-related pathways exhibited significant negative ES values, \n",
    "strongly suggesting a pattern of immune suppression—or \"immune evasion\"—in patients who experienced tumor relapse."
   ]
  }
